Detailed
Agile is well suited for modern, fast-changing projects that require flexibility, innovation, and continuous
feedback. Waterfall remains effective for projects with well-defined and stable requirements. Choosing the
appropriate methodology depends on project goals, complexity, risk tolerance, and stakeholder expectations.
Many organizations adopt hybrid approaches to combine the strengths of both methodologies.
